gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Warriors 113, Suns 112
gameRecap.excerpt: Stephen Curry knocked down a turnaround three-pointer with 0.7 seconds remaining in regulation to lift the Warriors over the Suns, 113-112. Curry recorded 30 points (9-16 3pt. FG), nine rebounds and six assists for the Warriors, while Jonathan Kuminga added 21 points and five rebounds in the victory. Devin Booker (32 points, six assists) and Kevin Durant (24 points, 10 rebounds, seven assists) combined for 56 points for the Suns in the losing effort. The Warriors win their fourth straight game as they improve to 25-25 on the season, while the Suns fall to 31-22.
